    "instruction": "Load metric.csv and trace.csv from the working directory. For metric.csv: aggregate by (cmdb_id, kpi_name) and produce a compact table with columns [cmdb_id, kpi_name, count, min_timestamp, max_timestamp, p95_value] where p95_value is the global 95th percentile of 'value' for that component-KPI using the full series in the file. Sort the result by count descending and return up to 50 rows. For trace.csv: aggregate by (cmdb_id, trace_name) and produce a compact table with columns [cmdb_id, trace_name, count, min_timestamp, max_timestamp, p95_value] where p95_value is the global 95th percentile of 'value' for that component-trace_name. Sort by count descending and return up to 50 rows. Also report the overall min and max timestamp across each file. Return results as plain text tables (no plots) and keep outputs compact."
